Nor can they grow their way out of them. The only solutions are massive inflation, currency debasement or default.

With $250+ trillion of global debt and $65+ trillion of domestic public and private sector U.S. debt, there is simply no way to plausibly contend that the global or U.S. economies can service or repay these obligations.
The post-crisis recovery was based on an explosion of both domestic and global debt.
While everyone was celebrating strong GDP growth of $1.3 trillion in 2018, America’s debt also grew by $1.3 trillion. Ignorance may feel like bliss, but more bliss like that is going to sting.
